JK", "POSA.JK", "TRIO.JK", "PEGE.JK", "INCI.JK", "SEMA.JK", "TNCA.JK", "GTSI.JK", "PEVE.JK", "TRIL.JK", "PNSE.JK", "IOTF.JK", "MRAT.JK", "ARKA.JK", "CHIP.JK", "YELO.JK", "PORT.JK", "MAGP.JK", "HADE.JK", "IBOS.JK", "TIRA.JK", "PSDN.JK", "MAPB.JK", "ASJT.JK", "BIPP.JK", "CTBN.JK", "VOKS.JK", "SONA.JK", "VKTR.JK", "BSML.JK", "RELF.JK", "LMPI.JK", "NEST.JK", "KBAG.JK", "DEPO.JK", "IPPE.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-18T11:54:20", "title": "Goto Gojek Tokopedia's shares see high trading volume and price surge in inaugural session."}, {"body": "Boy Thohir increased his stake in PT Provident Investasi Bersama Tbk (PROV) to nearly 20% by purchasing 373.75 million shares, while other investors made notable transactions, including DBS Bank Ltd's purchase of 6.29% of PT Sarimelati Kencana Tbk (PZZA) and CGS International Securities Singapore Pte Ltd's acquisition of 116.95 million shares of PT Astrindo Nusantara Infrastruktur Tbk (BIPI). Meanwhile, HSBC-Fund Svs A/C Chengdong Investment Corp-Self sold 64.70 million shares of PT Bumi Resources Tbk (BUMI), marking the largest share sale of the period.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 65, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51786/boy-thohir-increases-stake-provident-investasi-bersama-palm-shares", "sub_sector": ["holding-investment-companies", "consumer-services", "oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "IDX", "Executive Changes", "Mergers & Acquisitions", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["PALM.JK", "PZZA.JK", "BIPI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-18T11:49:00", "title": "Several investors make notable transactions in Indonesian companies, including purchases and sales of shares in various industries."}, {"body": "PT Pertamina Geothermal Tbk (PGeo) and PT Pembangunan Aceh are targeting to start geothermal drilling in the Seulawah Agam area, Aceh, in 2025, with an estimated potential of 320 megawatts, which is expected to boost PGeo's stock performance. The project is currently in the land acquisition process, with the Aceh government committed to supporting the development while prioritizing the environment and people.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 1, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 65, "sector": "infrastructures", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51785/pgeo-targets-seulawah-agam-drilling", "sub_sector": ["utilities"], "tags": ["Energy Commodities", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["PGEO.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-18T11:11:33", "title": "Pertamina Geothermal and Pembangunan Aceh to Launch Geothermal Drilling Project in Aceh in 2025"}, {"body": "PT Cakra Buana Resources Energi Tbk (CBRE) has signed a 5-year lease contract for a bulk carrier supramax vessel, expected to generate IDR 264.62 billion in revenue, with a daily charter rate of IDR 145 million. The contract is expected to bring in IDR 52.92 billion in revenue in 2025, reinforcing the company's financial condition, and adding to its existing revenue streams from time charter, freight charter, and ship management.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51784/leasing-vessel-cbre-scores-idr", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Market Trends", "Earnings Report", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["CBRE.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-18T10:18:56", "title": "PT Cakra Buana Resources Energi to Lease Bulk Carrier Vessel, Expecting IDR 264.62 Billion in Revenue Over 5 Years."}, {"body": "PT Alamtri Resources Indonesia Tbk (ADRO) has announced an interim dividend distribution of USD 200 million, despite a significant 7.72% drop in its share price over the past week, with the dividend to be disbursed on January 15, 2025. As of September 30, 2024, ADRO reported a net profit of USD 1.18 billion and unrestricted retained earnings of USD 5.93 billion.", "dimension": {"dividend": 2, "financials": 1, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51778/week-adro-promises-dividend", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Dividends", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["ADRO.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-17T16:46:48", "title": "PT Alamtri Resources Indonesia to Distribute USD 200 Million Interim Dividend Despite Recent Stock Price Drop"}, {"body": "BP2S SG/BNP Paribas Singapore Branch Wealth Management acquired 400 million shares of PT Citra Marga Nusaphala Persada Tbk (CMNP), increasing its ownership stake to nearly 60%, while Mataram Limited acquired 400 million shares of PT SLJ Global Tbk, increasing its ownership stake to 15%. Other notable transactions include PT Saratoga Investama Sedaya Tbk acquiring 53.36 million shares of PT Merdeka Copper Gold Tbk, and HSBC-Fund Svs A/C Chengdong Investment Corp-Self selling 78.90 million shares of PT Bumi Resources Tbk.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51772/bps-sgbnp-paribas-claims-cmnp-acquiring-shares", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials", "holding-investment-companies", "basic-materials"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Executive Changes", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["SULI.JK", "SRTG.JK", "MDKA.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-17T12:31:29", "title": "Multiple major share acquisitions and sales occur in Indonesian companies across various industries."}, {"body": "PT Triputra Agro Persada Tbk (TAPG) welcomed two new significant investors, PT Daya Adicipta Mustika and T. Permadi Rachmat, who purchased 1.17 billion and 1.03 billion shares, respectively, increasing their stakes to 6% and 5.19%. Meanwhile, other investors, including PT Persada Capital Investama, PT Triputra Investindo Arya, and Garibaldi Thohir, increased their stakes in TAPG, while PT Saratoga Sentra Business sold shares, resulting in a 2.15% decrease in its stake.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-non-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51771/triputra-agro-persada-tapg-welcomed-key-investors", "sub_sector": ["food-beverage"], "tags": ["Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "IDX", "Executive Changes", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["TAPG.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-17T11:39:33", "title": "PT Triputra Agro Persada TBK sees significant changes in ownership structure with new investors purchasing shares."}, {"body": "PT Petrosea TBK (PTRO) saw its stock price fluctuate between IDR 25,625 and IDR 25,925 per share after securing shareholder approval for a 1:10 stock split plan, which will split one IDR 50 share into 10 shares worth IDR 5 each. The company now has 1 billion shares, with controllers holding 54.48% and free float shares accounting for 26.43% of the total.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51770/stock-split-greenlit-ptro-decline-price-morning", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Stock Splits", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["PTRO.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-17T11:29:15", "title": "PT Petrosea's stock price fluctuates after shareholders approve 1:10 stock split plan."}, {"body": "PT Raharja Energi Cepu TBK (RATU) plans to debut on the Indonesia Stock Exchange with an initial public offering of 543.01 million shares, priced between IDR 900-1,150 per share, potentially raising IDR 624.46 billion. After the IPO, PT Rukun Raharja TBK (RAJA) will remain RATU's controlling shareholder with 79.99% ownership, while public investors will hold 20% and PT Rukun Prima Sarana will hold 0.004%.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51769/ratu-sets-ipo-shares-rajas-divested-shares", "sub_sector": ["alternative-energy"], "tags": ["IDX", "IPO", "IDX Composite", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-12-17T11:14:19", "title": "Ratu to Raise IDR 624.46 Billion in IPO with Offering of 543.01 Million Shares on Indonesia Stock Exchange."}, {"body": "PT Ancara Logistics Indonesia Tbk (ALII) has increased its stake in subsidiary PT Mahakam Coal Terminal to 78.12% through the issuance of 342,000 new shares, raising IDR 342 billion to settle debts with OCP Asia Fund IV and V Pte Ltd earlier than scheduled. The funds will be used to speed up the settlement of a USD 62 million term loan obtained on June 14, 2023, with PT Bank Mandiri Tbk providing a credit facility worth IDR 342 billion to boost ALII's capital.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51768/securing-loans-alii-raises-stakes-subsidiary", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal", "banks"], "tags": ["Debt", "Bonds", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Executive Changes", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["ALII.JK", "BMRI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-17T10:59:54", "title": "Ancara Logistics increases stake in Mahakam Coal Terminal to 78.12% through new share issuance to settle debts."}]